(thirdQuint)Effectiveness and Safety of New Botanical Component-LFCO- Compared With Existing TTO in Clinical Study.

 Screening of natural compounds for the development of anti-acne therapeutic agents has been steadily required considering various side effects of acne medications.

However, previous studies have mainly focused on experimental tests without clinical trials and histopathological analysis.

 To compare the clinical efficacy, safety and histopathological changes between Lactobacillus fermented Chamaecypris obtusa (LFCO) and existing tea tree oil (TTO) Total thirty four patients were instructed to apply 5 % LFCO to the involved areas of randomly allocated side and 5 % TTO extract to the other side for 8 weeks in a double blind split-face clinical trial.

